  "root_text": {
    "snp3.2:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 3.2 ",
    "snp3.2:0.2": "Padhānasutta ",
    "snp3.2:1.1": "“Taṁ maṁ padhānapahitattaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:1.2": "nadiṁ nerañjaraṁ pati; ",
    "snp3.2:1.3": "Viparakkamma jhāyantaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:1.4": "yogakkhemassa pattiyā. ",
    "snp3.2:2.1": "Namucī karuṇaṁ vācaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:2.2": "bhāsamāno upāgami; ",
    "snp3.2:2.3": "‘Kiso tvamasi dubbaṇṇo, ",
    "snp3.2:2.4": "santike maraṇaṁ tava. ",
    "snp3.2:3.1": "Sahassabhāgo maraṇassa, ",
    "snp3.2:3.2": "ekaṁso tava jīvitaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:3.3": "Jīva bho jīvitaṁ seyyo, ",
    "snp3.2:3.4": "jīvaṁ puññāni kāhasi. ",
    "snp3.2:4.1": "Carato ca te brahmacariyaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:4.2": "Aggihuttañca jūhato; ",
    "snp3.2:4.3": "Pahūtaṁ cīyate puññaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:4.4": "Kiṁ padhānena kāhasi. ",
    "snp3.2:5.1": "Duggo maggo padhānāya, ",
    "snp3.2:5.2": "dukkaro durabhisambhavo’”; ",
    "snp3.2:5.3": "Imā gāthā bhaṇaṁ māro, ",
    "snp3.2:5.4": "aṭṭhā buddhassa santike. ",
    "snp3.2:6.1": "Taṁ tathāvādinaṁ māraṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:6.2": "bhagavā etadabravi; ",
    "snp3.2:6.3": "“Pamattabandhu pāpima, ",
    "snp3.2:6.4": "yenatthena idhāgato. ",
    "snp3.2:7.1": "Aṇumattopi puññena, ",
    "snp3.2:7.2": "Attho mayhaṁ na vijjati; ",
    "snp3.2:7.3": "Yesañca attho puññena, ",
    "snp3.2:7.4": "Te māro vattumarahati. ",
    "snp3.2:8.1": "Atthi saddhā tathā viriyaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:8.2": "paññā ca mama vijjati; ",
    "snp3.2:8.3": "Evaṁ maṁ pahitattampi, ",
    "snp3.2:8.4": "kiṁ jīvamanupucchasi. ",
    "snp3.2:9.1": "Nadīnamapi sotāni, ",
    "snp3.2:9.2": "ayaṁ vāto visosaye; ",
    "snp3.2:9.3": "Kiñca me pahitattassa, ",
    "snp3.2:9.4": "lohitaṁ nupasussaye. ",
    "snp3.2:10.1": "Lohite sussamānamhi, ",
    "snp3.2:10.2": "Pittaṁ semhañca sussati; ",
    "snp3.2:10.3": "Maṁsesu khīyamānesu, ",
    "snp3.2:10.4": "Bhiyyo cittaṁ pasīdati; ",
    "snp3.2:10.5": "Bhiyyo sati ca paññā ca, ",
    "snp3.2:10.6": "Samādhi mama tiṭṭhati. ",
    "snp3.2:11.1": "Tassa mevaṁ viharato, ",
    "snp3.2:11.2": "Pattassuttamavedanaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:11.3": "Kāmesu nāpekkhate cittaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:11.4": "Passa sattassa suddhataṁ. ",
    "snp3.2:12.1": "Kāmā te paṭhamā senā, ",
    "snp3.2:12.2": "Dutiyā arati vuccati; ",
    "snp3.2:12.3": "Tatiyā khuppipāsā te, ",
    "snp3.2:12.4": "Catutthī taṇhā pavuccati. ",
    "snp3.2:13.1": "Pañcamaṁ thinamiddhaṁ te, ",
    "snp3.2:13.2": "Chaṭṭhā bhīrū pavuccati; ",
    "snp3.2:13.3": "Sattamī vicikicchā te, ",
    "snp3.2:13.4": "Makkho thambho te aṭṭhamo. ",
    "snp3.2:14.1": "Lābho siloko sakkāro, ",
    "snp3.2:14.2": "Micchāladdho ca yo yaso; ",
    "snp3.2:14.3": "Yo cattānaṁ samukkaṁse, ",
    "snp3.2:14.4": "Pare ca avajānati. ",
    "snp3.2:15.1": "Esā namuci te senā, ",
    "snp3.2:15.2": "Kaṇhassābhippahārinī; ",
    "snp3.2:15.3": "Na naṁ asūro jināti, ",
    "snp3.2:15.4": "Jetvā ca labhate sukhaṁ. ",
    "snp3.2:16.1": "Esa muñjaṁ parihare, ",
    "snp3.2:16.2": "Dhiratthu mama jīvitaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:16.3": "Saṅgāme me mataṁ seyyo, ",
    "snp3.2:16.4": "Yañce jīve parājito. ",
    "snp3.2:17.1": "Pagāḷhettha na dissanti, ",
    "snp3.2:17.2": "Eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā; ",
    "snp3.2:17.3": "Tañca maggaṁ na jānanti, ",
    "snp3.2:17.4": "Yena gacchanti subbatā. ",
    "snp3.2:18.1": "Samantā dhajiniṁ disvā, ",
    "snp3.2:18.2": "Yuttaṁ māraṁ savāhanaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:18.3": "Yuddhāya paccuggacchāmi, ",
    "snp3.2:18.4": "Mā maṁ ṭhānā acāvayi. ",
    "snp3.2:19.1": "Yaṁ te taṁ nappasahati, ",
    "snp3.2:19.2": "Senaṁ loko sadevako; ",
    "snp3.2:19.3": "Taṁ te paññāya bhecchāmi, ",
    "snp3.2:19.4": "Āmaṁ pattaṁva asmanā. ",
    "snp3.2:20.1": "Vasīkaritvā saṅkappaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:20.2": "Satiñca sūpatiṭṭhitaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:20.3": "Raṭṭhā raṭṭhaṁ vicarissaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:20.4": "Sāvake vinayaṁ puthū. ",
    "snp3.2:21.1": "Te appamattā pahitattā, ",
    "snp3.2:21.2": "Mama sāsanakārakā; ",
    "snp3.2:21.3": "Akāmassa te gamissanti, ",
    "snp3.2:21.4": "Yattha gantvā na socare”. ",
    "snp3.2:22.1": "“Satta vassāni bhagavantaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:22.2": "Anubandhiṁ padāpadaṁ; ",
    "snp3.2:22.3": "Otāraṁ nādhigacchissaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:22.4": "Sambuddhassa satīmato. ",
    "snp3.2:23.1": "Medavaṇṇaṁva pāsāṇaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:23.2": "Vāyaso anupariyagā; ",
    "snp3.2:23.3": "Apettha muduṁ vindema, ",
    "snp3.2:23.4": "Api assādanā siyā. ",
    "snp3.2:24.1": "Aladdhā tattha assādaṁ, ",
    "snp3.2:24.2": "Vāyasetto apakkami; ",
    "snp3.2:24.3": "Kākova selamāsajja, ",
    "snp3.2:24.4": "Nibbijjāpema gotamaṁ”. ",
    "snp3.2:25.1": "Tassa sokaparetassa, ",
    "snp3.2:25.2": "Vīṇā kacchā abhassatha; ",
    "snp3.2:25.3": "Tato so dummano yakkho, ",
    "snp3.2:25.4": "Tatthevantaradhāyathāti. ",
    "snp3.2:25.5": "Padhānasuttaṁ dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp3.2:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 3.2 ",
    "snp3.2:0.2": "Striving ",
    "snp3.2:1.1": "“During my time of resolute striving ",
    "snp3.2:1.2": "back on the bank of the Nerañjara River, ",
    "snp3.2:1.3": "I was meditating very hard ",
    "snp3.2:1.4": "for the sake of sanctuary from the yoke. ",
    "snp3.2:2.1": "Namucī approached, ",
    "snp3.2:2.2": "speaking words of kindness: ",
    "snp3.2:2.3": "‘You’re thin, discolored, ",
    "snp3.2:2.4": "on the verge of death. ",
    "snp3.2:3.1": "Death has a thousand parts of you, ",
    "snp3.2:3.2": "one fraction is left to life. ",
    "snp3.2:3.3": "Live worthy sir! Life is better! ",
    "snp3.2:3.4": "Living, you can make merits. ",
    "snp3.2:4.1": "While leading the spiritual life ",
    "snp3.2:4.2": "and serving the sacred flame, ",
    "snp3.2:4.3": "you can pile up abundant merit—",
    "snp3.2:4.4": "so what will striving do for you? ",
    "snp3.2:5.1": "Hard to walk is the path of striving, ",
    "snp3.2:5.2": "hard to do, a hard challenge to win.’” ",
    "snp3.2:5.3": "These are the verses Māra spoke ",
    "snp3.2:5.4": "as he stood beside the Buddha. ",
    "snp3.2:6.1": "When Māra had spoken in this way, ",
    "snp3.2:6.2": "the Buddha said this: ",
    "snp3.2:6.3": "“O Wicked One, kinsman of the negligent, ",
    "snp3.2:6.4": "you’re here for your own purpose. ",
    "snp3.2:7.1": "I have no need for ",
    "snp3.2:7.2": "the slightest bit of merit. ",
    "snp3.2:7.3": "Those with need for merit ",
    "snp3.2:7.4": "are fit for Māra to address. ",
    "snp3.2:8.1": "I have faith and energy too, ",
    "snp3.2:8.2": "and wisdom is found in me. ",
    "snp3.2:8.3": "When I am so resolute, ",
    "snp3.2:8.4": "why do you beg me to live? ",
    "snp3.2:9.1": "The rivers and streams ",
    "snp3.2:9.2": "might be dried by the wind, ",
    "snp3.2:9.3": "so why, when I am resolute, ",
    "snp3.2:9.4": "should it not dry up my blood? ",
    "snp3.2:10.1": "And while the blood is drying up, ",
    "snp3.2:10.2": "the bile and phlegm dry too. ",
    "snp3.2:10.3": "And as my muscles waste away, ",
    "snp3.2:10.4": "my mind grows more serene. ",
    "snp3.2:10.5": "And all the stronger grow mindfulness ",
    "snp3.2:10.6": "and wisdom and immersion. ",
    "snp3.2:11.1": "As I meditate like this, ",
    "snp3.2:11.2": "having attained the supreme feeling, ",
    "snp3.2:11.3": "my mind has no interest in sensual pleasures: ",
    "snp3.2:11.4": "behold a being’s purity! ",
    "snp3.2:12.1": "Sensual pleasures are your first army, ",
    "snp3.2:12.2": "the second is called discontent, ",
    "snp3.2:12.3": "hunger and thirst are the third, ",
    "snp3.2:12.4": "and the fourth is said to be craving. ",
    "snp3.2:13.1": "Your fifth is dullness and drowsiness, ",
    "snp3.2:13.2": "the sixth is said to be cowardice, ",
    "snp3.2:13.3": "your seventh is doubt, ",
    "snp3.2:13.4": "contempt and obstinacy are your eighth. ",
    "snp3.2:14.1": "Profit, praise, and honor, ",
    "snp3.2:14.2": "and misbegotten fame; ",
    "snp3.2:14.3": "the extolling of oneself ",
    "snp3.2:14.4": "while scorning others. ",
    "snp3.2:15.1": "This is your army, Namucī, ",
    "snp3.2:15.2": "the strike force of the Dark One. ",
    "snp3.2:15.3": "Only a hero can defeat it, ",
    "snp3.2:15.4": "but in victory there lies bliss. ",
    "snp3.2:16.1": "Let me gird myself—",
    "snp3.2:16.2": "curse my life! ",
    "snp3.2:16.3": "I’d rather die in battle ",
    "snp3.2:16.4": "than live on in defeat. ",
    "snp3.2:17.1": "Here some ascetics and brahmins ",
    "snp3.2:17.2": "are swallowed up, not to be seen again. ",
    "snp3.2:17.3": "And they do not know the path ",
    "snp3.2:17.4": "traveled by those true to their vows. ",
    "snp3.2:18.1": "Seeing Māra ready on his mount, ",
    "snp3.2:18.2": "surrounded by his bannered forces, ",
    "snp3.2:18.3": "I shall meet them in battle—",
    "snp3.2:18.4": "they’ll never make me retreat! ",
    "snp3.2:19.1": "That army of yours has never been beaten ",
    "snp3.2:19.2": "by the world with all its gods. ",
    "snp3.2:19.3": "Yet I shall smash it with wisdom, ",
    "snp3.2:19.4": "like an unfired pot with a stone. ",
    "snp3.2:20.1": "Having brought my thoughts under control, ",
    "snp3.2:20.2": "and established mindfulness well, ",
    "snp3.2:20.3": "I shall wander from country to country, ",
    "snp3.2:20.4": "guiding many disciples. ",
    "snp3.2:21.1": "Diligent and resolute, ",
    "snp3.2:21.2": "following my instructions, ",
    "snp3.2:21.3": "they will proceed despite your will, ",
    "snp3.2:21.4": "to where there is no sorrow.” ",
    "snp3.2:22.1": "“For seven years I followed ",
    "snp3.2:22.2": "step by step behind the Blessed One. ",
    "snp3.2:22.3": "I found no vulnerability ",
    "snp3.2:22.4": "in the mindful Awakened One. ",
    "snp3.2:23.1": "A crow once circled a stone ",
    "snp3.2:23.2": "that looked like a lump of fat. ",
    "snp3.2:23.3": "‘Perhaps I’ll find something tender,’ it thought, ",
    "snp3.2:23.4": "‘perhaps there’s something tasty.’ ",
    "snp3.2:24.1": "But finding nothing tasty, ",
    "snp3.2:24.2": "the crow left that place. ",
    "snp3.2:24.3": "Like the crow that pecked the stone, ",
    "snp3.2:24.4": "I leave Gotama disappointed.” ",
    "snp3.2:25.1": "So stricken with sorrow ",
    "snp3.2:25.2": "that his harp dropped from his armpit, ",
    "snp3.2:25.3": "that spirit, downcast, ",
    "snp3.2:25.4": "vanished right there. "
  },
